body,

h2 {

h3 {

.section {

  margin-right: auto;
  height: 100%;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
}

#conversionResources .section,

#masthead .section {

}

  }

  }

/** HEADER **/
.header {
  background: #fff;
  border-bottom: 6px solid #dc0132;
  width: 100%;
  height: 86px;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

.header-imgContainer {
  height: 100%;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}

.header-imgContainer img {
  width: 555px;
  height: 48px;
}
@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  .header-imgContainer img {
    width: 280px;
    height: 24.22px;
  }
}
  
/**  MASTHEAD  **/
#masthead {
  display: block;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
  background-image: url(//d9hhrg4mnvzow.cloudfront.net/more.umb.com/ruralking/38330f07-rk-hero.jpg);
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-position: bottom;
  background-size: contain;
  border-style: none;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
  margin-bottom: 0px;
  border-radius: 0px;
  width: 100%;
  height: 480px;
  position: relative;
}

#masthead p {
  color: #000a23;
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 24px;
  padding: 5px 0px;
  line-height: 33px;
}

#welcomeLogo {
  width: 770px;
}

#rewardsContainer {
  height: auto;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  justify-content: center;
  margin: 20px 0;
}

.rewardPercentage {
  width: 135px;
  padding: 0 20px;
}

#threePercent,
#onePercent {
  border-left: 1px solid;
}

#masthead #rewardsContainer p.percentText {
  font-size: 16px;
  text-align: left;
  font-weight: 600;
  padding: 0;
  line-height: 22px;
}

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  #masthead {
    background-image: url(//d9hhrg4mnvzow.cloudfront.net/more.umb.com/ruralking/542d2685-rk-hero-mobile.jpg);
  }

  #welcomeLogo {
    content: url(//d9hhrg4mnvzow.cloudfront.net/more.umb.com/ruralking/a1cd76ed-rk-headline-welcome-mobile.svg);
    width: 320px;
  }

  #masthead p {
    font-size: 20px;
    padding: 0;
    line-height: 26px;
  }

  #rewardsContainer {
    display: none;
  }
}

/**  HIGHLIGHTED SECTION **/
#rkHighlight .section p {
  padding: 45px 251px 33px 251px;
  text-align: center;
  line-height: 28px;
  font-size: 18px;
}

#rkHighlight #highlights {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  margin-bottom: 45px;
}

#rkHighlight #highlights h4 {
  padding: 0 30px;
  font-weight: 600;
}

#rkHighlight #highlights img {
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
  margin-top: 12px;
}

@media screen and (max-width: 1199px) {
  #rkHighlight .section p {
    padding: 45px 6rem 33px 6rem;
  }
}

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  #rkHighlight .section p {
    padding: 45px 0 33px;
    line-height: 26px;
  }

  #rkHighlight #highlights {
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  #rkHighlight #highlights img {
    margin: 10px 0;
  }

  #rkHighlight #highlights h4 {
    font-size: 22px;
  }
}

/** IMPORTANT DATES, NEWS, & TIPS **/
#importantDates {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  padding-top: 70px;
}

#importantDates #datesContainer {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  margin: 25px 0 50px;
}
  
#datesContainer h4 {
    padding-bottom: 5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 20px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
}  

#importantDates #datesContainer .date {
  flex-direction: column;
  text-align: center;
  margin: 0 20px;
}

#importantDates #datesContainer .date p {
  width: 220px;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 26px;
}

#importantDates #datesContainer .date img {
  width: 90px;
  height: 90px;
}

#newsContainer {
  text-align: center;
  background-color: #fff;
  box-shadow: 0px 3px 6px #00000029;
  border: 1px solid #516271;
  padding: 20px 160px 40px;
  /* margin: 50px 0; */
  margin-bottom: 50px;
}

#newsItems div {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
}

#newsContainer p {
  padding: 10px 0;
}

#newsContainer p span {
  margin-right: 16px;
}

#tipsContainer {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 80px;
}

#tipsContainer #tips p {
  padding: 10px 0;
  text-indent: -32px;
  padding-left: 32px;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 24px;
}

#tipsContainer #tips p::before {
  content: "";
  background: url(//d9hhrg4mnvzow.cloudfront.net/more.umb.com/ruralking/855a0d28-rk-icon-checkmark.svg) no-repeat;
  display: inline-block;
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
  margin-right: 15px;
}

#tipsContainer #tips {
  text-align: left;
  width: 900px;
}

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  #importantDates #datesContainer {
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  #tipsContainer {
    margin-bottom: 55px;
  }

  #tipsContainer #tips {
    width: auto;
  }

  #newsContainer {
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  #newsItems {
    padding: 0 25px;
  }

  #newsItems div {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    flex-direction: column;
    text-align: left;
  }

  #newsContainer p {
    padding: 3px 0;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 24px;
  }
}

/** MORE INFOMATION **/

#moreInfo {
  margin: 80px 0;
}

button.infoTab {
  background-color: #d6dce2;
  color: #000a23;
  font-size: 16px;
  border: none;
  padding: 12px 38px;
  width: 306px;
  height: 68px;
}

button.infoTab:hover, button.infoTab:focus {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  text-decoration: underline;
  cursor: pointer;
}

#infoTabsItems {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: flex-end;
  list-style: none;
}

#infoTabsContainer ul li {
  margin: 0 12px;
}

#infoTabsContainer #infoTabsItems li.active button.infoTab {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  border: 1px solid #75808c;
  font-weight: 600;
}

#infoTabsContainer #infoTabsItems li.active::before {
  content: "";
  position: relative;
  display: block;
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  bottom: -78px;
  right: -145px;
  background: #f2f2f2;
  border-right: solid 1px #75808c;
  border-bottom: solid 1px #75808c;
  transform: rotateZ(45deg);
}

#infoDetails {
  padding: 0 20px;
  margin-bottom: 25px;
  font-size: 18px;
  line-height: 28px;
}
  
@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  #infoDetails {
    text-align: center;
  }
}

.infoContent {
  width: 940px;
  margin-left: 12px;
  margin-top: 45px;
}

#infoAccordionContainer .infoContent {
  margin-top: 21px;
}

#infoTabsContainer .infoContent h4,
#infoAccordionContainer .infoContent h4 {
  color: #000a23;
  margin-bottom: 25px;
  font-size: 28px;
  line-height: 34px;
}

#infoTabsContainer .infoContent p,
#infoAccordionContainer .infoContent p {
  margin: 12px 0;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 22px;
}

#infoTabsContainer #newRewardsContent li,
#infoAccordionContainer .accordion-menu__sublist li {
  font-family: "Open Sans", sans-serif;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  list-style-type: disc;
}

#infoTabsContainer #newRewardsContent ul {
  margin-left: 25px;
}

#infoAccordionContainer .accordion-menu__sublist ul {
  list-style-type: disc;
  margin-left: 30px;
  overflow-wrap: break-word;
}

#infoAccordionContainer {
  display: none;
}

#infoTabsContainer {
  display: block;
}
  
.infoContent #rk-chart-img-d {
  width: 560px;
} 
  
.infoContent #rk-chart-img-m {
    width: 100%;
}  

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  .infoContent {
    width: auto;
  }

  #infoAccordionContainer {
    display: block;
  }
  #infoTabsContainer {
    display: none;
  }
  
}

/** CONVERSION RESOURCES **/
#conversionResources {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  height: 365px;
}

#conversionResources h2 {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 34px;
  font-family: "Roboto Slab", "Roboto", sans-serif;
  letter-spacing: 0px;
  color: #dc0132;
}

#conversionResources li {
  list-style-type: none;
}

.document {
  background: url(//d9hhrg4mnvzow.cloudfront.net/more.umb.com/ruralking/8fd49cad-rk-icon-document.svg) no-repeat left top;
  height: 20px;
  padding-top: 5px;
  padding-left: 30px;
}

#conversionResources .section > div {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  text-align: center;
  width: 65%;
}

#conversionResources ul {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  flex-direction: row;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  padding: 12px 0;

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  #conversionResources ul {
    padding: 0;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  #conversionResources ul:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  #conversionResources {
    height: auto;
  }

  .document {
    margin-bottom: 30px;
    align-self: auto;
    text-align: left;
    padding-left: 40px;
  }
  #conversionResources .section > div {
    width: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
}
  
#customerService {
    background-color: #546270;
    height: 365px;
}

#customerService .section {
    justify-content: center;
}

#customerService .section > div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    text-align: center;
    width: 65%;
}

#customerService h2 {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 34px;
    font-family: "Roboto Slab", "Roboto", sans-serif;
    letter-spacing: 0px;
    color: #FFF;
}

#customerService .tfn-container {
    display:flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    justify-content: space-evenly;
    margin-top: 35px;
}

#customerService .tfn-container .tfn-content{
    flex-direction: column;
}

#customerService .tfn-container .tfn-content h3 span{
    font-size: 20px;
    font-family: "Open Sans", sans-serif;
    line-height: 28px;
}

#customerService .tfn-container .tfn-content p{
    color: #FFF;
    line-height: 25px;
}  
  
@media screen and (max-width: 600px){
   #customerService {
     height: auto;
   }
  #customerService h2 {
    font-size: 32px;
  }
  #customerService .section > div {
    width: 100%;
    margin: 25px 0;
  } 
  #customerService .tfn-container {
    flex-direction: column;
  }  
  #customerService .tfn-container div.tfn-content:not(:first-child) {
   margin-top: 35px;
}  
}  

/**  FOOTER & DISCLAIMER **/
#footer {
  display: block;
  background: #546270;
  border-style: none;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
  margin-bottom: 0px;
  border-radius: 0px;
  width: 100%;
  height: 222px;
  position: relative;
}

#footer h3 {
  font-size: 26px;
}

#footer #connectBtn {
  background: #ef1732;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 12px 25px;
  margin-top: 25px;
  font-size: 22px;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-family: "Open Sans", sans-serif;
  font-weight: 600;
}

#disclaimer .section {
  width: 940px;
}

#disclaimer ol li {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-family: "Open Sans", sans-serif;
  list-style-type: decimal;
  margin-left: 16px;
}

#disclaimerContent {
  margin-top: 50px;
}

.copyright {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-family: "Open Sans", sans-serif;
  margin: 30px 0;
}

.copyright p {
  margin: 5px 0;
}

.red-line {
  border-top: 6px solid #dc0132;
}

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  #footer h3 {
    font-size: 22px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  #disclaimer .section {
    width: auto;
  }
}

/* Back To Top BTN */
#backTop {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 25px;
  right: 50px;
  z-index: 1;
}

#backTop button {
  border: none;
  background-color: transparent;
}

#backTop button:hover, #backTop button:focus {
  cursor: pointer;
}

#backTop button img {
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
}

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  #backTop {
    right: 20px;
  }

  #backTop button img {
    width: 26px;
    height: 26px;
  }
}

/** ACCORDION */
.accordion-menu--hidden {
  display: none;
}
.accordion-menu__list,
.accordion-menu__sublist {
  list-style-type: none;
}

.accordion-menu__link {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  background-color: #d6dce2;
  width: 100%;
  height: 68px;
  color: #000a23;
  font-family: "Open Sans", sans-serif;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 20px;
  text-decoration: none;
}
.accordion-menu__icon {
  position: relative;
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  transition: 0.2s all;
}
.accordion-menu__icon:before,
.accordion-menu__icon:after {
  content: "";
  display: block;
  background-color: #333;
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: -15px;
  transition: 0.35s;
  width: 100%;
  height: 2px;
}
.accordion-menu__icon:before {
  transform: translateY(-50%);
}
.accordion-menu__icon:after {
  transform: translateY(-50%) rotate(90deg);
}
.accordion-menu--active .accordion-menu__icon:before {
  transform: translateY(-50%) rotate(-90deg);
  opacity: 0;
}
.accordion-menu--active .accordion-menu__icon:after {
  transform: translateY(-50%) rotate(0);
}

.accordion-menu__sublink {
  display: block;
  padding-top: 1rem;
  padding-bottom: 1rem;
  border-bottom: 1px #eee solid;
}

.accordion-menu-nav {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding-bottom: 1rem;
  overflow: scroll;
}
.accordion-menu-nav__link:not(:last-child) {
  margin-right: 1rem;
}
.accordion-menu-wrapper {
  display: none;
}
.accordion-menu-wrapper.active {
  display: block;
}

li.accordion-menu__item {
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

a.accordion-menu__link.accordion-menu--active {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  border: 1px solid #75808c;
}

#infoAccordionContainer {
  width: 100%;
}

.accordion-menu__link span.label {
  width: 190px;
  padding-left: 15px;
}

</style><link rel="preload" href="" as="image"><script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
  const tabBtns = document.querySelectorAll(".infoTab");

  function switchInfoContent(tab) {
    let tabID = tab.getAttribute("id");
    let currentContent = document.querySelector("div:not(.hidden).infoContent");
    let selectedContent = document.getElementById(`${tabID}Content`);

    if (!tab.parentNode.classList.contains("active")) {
      //Update style of tab when active
      if (document.querySelector(".active")) {
        document.querySelector(".active").classList.remove("active");
      }

      tab.parentNode.classList.add("active");

      //Change Content
      if (selectedContent.classList.contains("hidden")) {
        currentContent.classList.add("hidden");
        selectedContent.classList.remove("hidden");
      }
    }
  }

  tabBtns.forEach(function (tab) {
    tab.addEventListener("click", function () {
      switchInfoContent(this);
    });
  });

  // Get the button:
  const arrowBtn = document.getElementById("arrowBtn");

  arrowBtn.addEventListener("click", backToTop);

  // When the user clicks on the button, scroll to the top of the document
  function backToTop() {
    document.body.scrollTop = 0; // For Safari

              </li>

            <div>
              <div class="infoContent" id="newCardContent">
                <h4>Receiving Your New Card</h4>
                <p><span>Updating Your Account With Redstone</span></p>
                <p>Make sure your <u>current</u> physical address, mailing address (if different from your physical address), email address, and phone numbers are correctly on file with your account at Redstone Federal Credit Union. This will help facilitate a smooth transition to your new credit card account.</p>
                <hr>
                <p><span>Receiving Your New Card</span></p>
                <p>Your new Rural King Rewards Visa credit card will arrive via mail.</p>
                <hr>
                <p><span>New Credit Card Appearance</span></p>
                <p>Your new credit card will look the same from the front. The core of your new UMB Bank issued card will be black. The back will show that it is issued by UMB Bank, n.a. with new phone number for customer service. </p>
                <hr>
                <p><span>Contactless Payments</span></p>
                <p>Your new Rural King Rewards Visa will be a contactless card. You will be able to tap the terminal with your card wherever you see the contactless sign and your payment will begin processing.</p>
              </div>
  
              <div class="infoContent hidden" id="onlineBankingContent">
                <h4>Online Banking, Billing, and Recurring Payments</h4>
                <p><span>Online Banking</span></p>
                <p>You will need to set up online access for your new Rural King Rewards Visa credit card. You will be able to access recent transactions, view statements, make payments, and more.</p>
                <hr>
                <p><span>Recurring Payments/Card-On-File</span></p>
                <p>You will need to update your card account number, expiration date and security code with merchants that you have authorized to store your current Rural King credit card account information for recurring and card-on-file transactions. You should update this information as soon as your new Rural King Rewards Visa credit card is activated.</p>
                <hr>  
                <p><span>Bank or Credit Union Bill Payment</span></p>
                <p>If your Rural King credit card is set-up to be paid using your bank’s online bill payment feature, you will need to delete the current Payee and add a new Payee using your new card account number and payment address.</p>
                <hr>  
                <p><span>Automatic Payments</span></p>
                <p>If you currently use automatic payments to pay your Rural King credit card, you will need to set-up new auto-payments.</p>
                <hr>  
                <p><span>Future-Dated Payments</span></p>
                <p>If you have payments to Redstone Federal Credit Union scheduled to pay after Thursday, March 21st, 2024, they will not process. You will need to re-schedule your future dated payments.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="infoContent hidden" id="newRewardsContent">
                <h4>New Rewards Program</h4>

                <p><span>Rural King Loyalty Rewards Program</span></p>
                <p>Rural King Rewards Visa credit cardholders must be a registered participant in Rural King’s Loyalty Rewards Program.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><p>Previously enrolled cardholders will automatically have their existing Rural King Rewards Loyalty number associated
                    with their new credit card</p></li>
                  <li><p>Unenrolled cardholders will be automatically enrolled and will have a new Rural King Rewards Loyalty number
                    associated with their new credit card</p></li>
                </ul>

                <hr>

                <p><span>Legacy Rewards</span></p>
                <p><b>The entire cash value</b> of legacy Rural King Visa credit card points <b>will automatically transfer over to new credit card accounts.</b> You may notice a difference in transferred point numbers; however, the cash equivalent of legacy rewards will carry forward. Transferred legacy rewards must be redeemed within 60 days of the date the reward was issued.</p>

                <hr> 

                <p><span>New Points are Worth Twice the Value</span></p>
                <p>Each point awarded under the new Rural King Rewards Visa credit card program is worth twice the cash value of a point
                  awarded through the legacy program! Examples of legacy program point value compared to new program point value are
                  illustrated below:</p>

                <p style="text-align: center;">

" id="rk-chart-img-d" alt="chart-points" />
                </p>

                <hr>

                <p><span>Earn More Points with Every Purchase</span></p>
                <p>Rural King Rewards Visa credit card Program Members can earn points by making qualified purchases:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><b>Five (5) Points</b> per dollar on Net Purchases made at Rural King store locations or RuralKing.com and Rural King affiliates,
                    subject to the Card Program Point Exclusions<sup>1</sup></li>
                  <li><b>Three (3) Points</b> per dollar on Net Purchases made at gas stations, restaurants, and fast food<sup>1</sup></li>
                  <li><b>Three (3) Points</b> per dollar on Net Purchases made up to $3,000 and one (1) Point per dollar on Net Purchases
                    made over $3,000 per calendar year at grocery stores<sup>1</sup></li>
                  <li><b>One (1) Point</b> per dollar on all other Net Purchases including Net Purchases made at in store clinics such as
                    Country Critters, and Net Purchases made from Rural King through third party websites (i.e. Amazon or Google
                    Express), subject to the Card Program Point Exclusions<sup>1</sup></li><br/>
                </ul>
                <p>For full details of the Rural King Rewards Visa Program Rules please see <a target="_blank" href="https://umb.com/RuralKingVisaRewardsProgramRules">https://umb.com/RuralKingVisaRewardsProgramRules</a></p>

                <hr>

                <p><span>Viewing and Redeeming Rewards</span></p>
                <p>New Rural King Rewards Visa credit card program members receive $5.00 for every 500 points, which may be redeemed at

                    <h4>Online Banking, Billing, and Recurring Payments</h4>
                    <p><span>Online Banking</span></p>
                    <p>You will need to set up online access for your new Rural King Rewards Visa credit card. You will be able to access recent transactions, view statements, make payments, and more.</p>
                    <hr>
                    <p><span>Recurring Payments/Card-On-File</span></p>
                    <p>You will need to update your card account number, expiration date and security code with merchants that you have authorized to store your current Rural King credit card account information for recurring and card-on-file transactions. You should update this information as soon as your new Rural King Rewards Visa credit card is activated.</p>
                    <hr>  
                    <p><span>Bank or Credit Union Bill Payment</span></p>
                    <p>If your Rural King credit card is set-up to be paid using your bank’s online bill payment feature, you will need to delete the current Payee and add a new Payee using your new card account number and payment address.</p>
                    <hr>  
                    <p><span>Automatic Payments</span></p>
                    <p>If you currently use automatic payments to pay your Rural King credit card, you will need to set-up new auto-payments.</p>
                    <hr>  
                    <p><span>Future-Dated Payments</span></p>
                    <p>If you have payments to Redstone Federal Credit Union scheduled to pay after Thursday, March 21st, 2024, they will not process. You will need to re-schedule your future dated payments.</p>

                <p>Rural King Rewards Visa credit cardholders must be a registered participant in Rural King’s Loyalty Rewards Program.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Previously enrolled cardholders will automatically have their existing Rural King Rewards Loyalty number associated
                    with their new credit card</li>
                  <li>Unenrolled cardholders will be automatically enrolled and will have a new Rural King Rewards Loyalty number
                    associated with their new credit card</li>
                </ul>

                <hr>

                <p><span>Legacy Rewards</span></p>
                <p><b>The entire cash value</b> of legacy Rural King Visa credit card points <b>will automatically transfer over to new credit card accounts.</b> You may notice a difference in transferred point numbers; however, the cash equivalent of legacy rewards will carry forward. Transferred legacy rewards must be redeemed within 60 days of the date the reward was issued.</p>

                <hr> 

                <p><span>New Points are Worth Twice the Value</span></p>
                <p>Each point awarded under the new Rural King Rewards Visa credit card program is worth twice the cash value of a point

                  illustrated below:</p>

" id="rk-chart-img-m" alt="chart-points" />
                </p>

                <hr>

                <p><span>Earn More Points with Every Purchase</span></p>
                <p>Rural King Rewards Visa credit card Program Members can earn points by making qualified purchases:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><b>Five (5) Points</b> per dollar on Net Purchases made at Rural King store locations, or RuralKing.com or RKguns.com
                    subject to the Card Program Point Exclusions1<sup>1</sup></li>
                  <li><b>Three (3) Points</b> per dollar on Net Purchases made at gas stations, restaurants, and fast food<sup>1</sup></li>
                  <li><b>Three (3) Points</b> per dollar on Net Purchases made up to $3,000 and one (1) Point per dollar on Net Purchases
                    made over $3,000 per calendar year at grocery stores<sup>1</sup></li>
                  <li><b>One (1) Point</b> per dollar on all other Net Purchases including Net Purchases made at in store clinics such as
                    Country Critters, and Net Purchases made from Rural King through third party websites (i.e. Amazon or Google
                    Express), subject to the Card Program Point Exclusions<sup>1</sup></li><br/>
                </ul>
                <p>For full details of the Rural King Rewards Visa Program Rules please see <a target="_blank" href="https://umb.com/RuralKingVisaRewardsProgramRules" style="word-wrap: break-word;">https://umb.com/RuralKingVisaRewardsProgramRules</a></p>

                <p><span>Viewing and Redeeming Rewards</span></p>
                <p>New Rural King Rewards Visa credit card program members receive $5.00 for every 500 points, which may be redeemed at
                  Rural King store locations, or ruralking.com or rkguns.com. Rewards will post automatically within 72 hours of meeting the
                  qualifying Point threshold. View and manage rewards anytime through RuralKing.com.</p>

                <li>Cardholders will earn five (5) Points per dollar on Net Purchases made at Rural King store locations, or ruralking.com and Rural King affliates, subject to the following limitations:<br><br>Cardholders will earn one (1) Point per dollar on all other Net Purchases including Net Purchases made at in store clinics such as Country Critters, and Net Purchases made from Rural King through third party websites (i.e. Amazon or Google Express), subject to the Card Program Point Exclusions. Card Program Point Exclusions: <br><br>Cardholders will not earn Points on a) Rural King store purchases that receive special financing; b) tractor purchases; c) the purchase of Rural King Gift Cards; and Visa, American Express or Mastercard gift/prepaid cards; d) taxes, bottle deposits, shipping, delivery, handling and all other fees or charges; e) Purchases made prior to the date the Card was issued; and f) where otherwise prohibited by law. <br><br>Issuer will use merchant identification numbers (MIDs) to identify Rural King and ruralking.com Net Purchases. <br><br>Cardholders will earn three (3) Points per dollar on Net Purchases made at Gas Stations, Grocery Stores, Restaurants, and Fast Food.
